  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "21:15-22 These events seem to have taken place towards the end of David's reign. David fainted, but he did not flee, and God sent help in the time of need. In spiritual conflicts, even strong saints sometimes wax faint; then Satan attacks them furiously; but those who stand their ground and resist him, shall be relieved and made more than conquerors. Death is a Christian's last enemy, and a son of Anak; but through Him that triumphed for us, believers shall be more than conquerors at last, even over that enemy.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Ishbi-benob - A corrupt reading. The whole passage should perhaps run thus: \"And David waxed faint. So they halted in Gob (as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 21:18-19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). And there was a man (in Gob) which was of the sons of the giant, etc.\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Sons of the giant - The \"giant\" here 2 Samuel 21:18, 2 Samuel 21:20, 2 Samuel 21:22 is \"ha-Raphah,\" whence, the \"Rephaim\" Genesis 14:5; Deuteronomy 2:11. The sons of Ha-raphah, or Rephaim, are different from the \"Nephilim,\" or Giants Genesis 6:4; Numbers 13:33. The sons of Anak were not strictly Rephaim, but Nephilim.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Sons of the giant - The \"giant\" here ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 21:18",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 21:20",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 21:22",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " is \"ha-Raphah,\" whence, the \"Rephaim\" ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 14:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 2:11",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The sons of Ha-raphah, or Rephaim, are different from the \"Nephilim,\" or Giants ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 6:4",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 13:33",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The sons of Anak were not strictly Rephaim, but Nephilim.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
